Text.SourceString: Hey, you! Is <Italic>this</> our new neighbor?//<portrait=normal>Going around town, huh? Have you been to the tavern yet?//<NPCName>Frank</> is there all the time. Have you two met?
Oh, he’s my husband! You know what, you should stop by our house sometime…//<portrait=normal><NPCName>Frank’ll</> cook us dinner. Gosh! That sounds wonderful. Yes! You can tell us your story!

Special.SourceString: Dude behind the bar? Yeah. Your friend?

Text.SourceString: Oh, he’s my husband! You know what, you should stop by our house sometime…//<portrait=normal><NPCName>Frank’ll</> cook us dinner. Gosh! That sounds wonderful. Yes! You can tell us your story!
That’s one complicated way of answering…//<portrait=happy>Anyway, he’s super friendly.

Special.SourceString: The bartender? Yes and no. Kind of. Depends on what you mean by “met.” Yes, I have seen him, but no, I haven’t actually spoken to him.

Text.SourceString: I really can’t smell anything near the trash pit. The recycling is sorted correctly, so there shouldn’t be a strong smell.//I know this because I’m the one who sorts everything out.
Oh, you agree? Well… Maybe it’s just the smell of old plastic that people are complaining about.
I really can’t smell anything near the trash pit.//I know the recycling is sorted correctly, so there shouldn’t be a strong smell.

Oh, for sure! Sometimes we forget to sort our recycling before tossing it into the bin.//<portrait=normal>That’s where I come in. I go through the bins now and then to make sure all the recycling is properly sorted.
Do you recycle at your farm, <PlayerName>$player</>?
You must get a lot of trash on your farm, huh?//We live next to the beach, and so much trash blows right up to the front of our garage.
Yikes!
<NpcName>Frank</> is way too busy to clean up the lot next to the house.

The weeds just keep growing and growing. Dear goodness!//<portrait=annoyed>It’s like somebody’s been dumping fertilizer on them or something. If <NpcName>Noah</> weren’t so uptight, I would say he’s been pranking us.
<NpcName>Frank</> is way too busy to clean up the lot next to the house.

The weeds just keep growing and growing. Dear goodness!//<portrait=annoyed>It’s like somebody’s been dumping fertilizer on them or something. If <NpcName>Noah</> weren’t so uptight, I would say he’s been pranking us.
I love kids…but my kids are my cats.//<portrait=happy>They’re the loves of our lives. You’ve seen them around, right? Aren’t they cute?
Listen, <PlayerName>$player</>, people like gifts. Even if they don’t celebrate birthdays, they still like getting gifts.//Trust me!
That’s just the way things are around here.
Talk to me, <PlayerName>$player</>. What’s going on with you today?
Listen, <PlayerName>$player</>, people like gifts. Even if they don’t celebrate birthdays, they still like getting gifts.//Trust me!
That’s just the way things are around here.
<NpcName>Sam </> likes his hair short. I shave his head every week!//<portrait=surprised>He’s a lousy tipper, though!
*laughs uncontrollably*
People should always tell the truth, because keeping track of lies is hard. It’s easier to just be who we are.
So, have you got any of these truths for me, <PlayerName>$player</>? Let’s hear it.
When one of my clients has a bad idea, I tell them.//I don’t want them walking around town with bad hair and people thinking it’s my fault!
Looking gorgeous as usual – just like an iris!//<portrait=happy>Ah, I love irises. *winks*
Looking gorgeous as usual – just like an iris!//<portrait=happy>Ah, I love irises. *winks*

<NpcName>Ling</> is your girl if you wanna know more about kelp, coral reef, and that stuff.//<portrait=happy><NpcName>Sunny</> and <NpcName>Jim</> can help with your fishing problem.//<portrait=normal>Hmm… What else… What else?
And the blacksmiths make weapons. But you already know that…
When one of my clients has a bad idea, I tell them.//I don’t want them walking around town with bad hair and people thinking it’s my fault!
I wish I could cut my own hair, but <NpcName>Emily</> does just fine.
She and <NpcName>Sam</> are the cutest couple. They’re such sweethearts!
I love catching up with <NpcName>Ben</>. He always has some insightful things to say.
<NpcName>Ben</> gets around, you know. He usually disappears the last two weeks of Fall.//<portrait=surprised>Who knows where he goes to?
I don’t go to the lake or wherever. Places like that are just too quiet for me.
I’ll totally lose my mind if I’m left alone with my thoughts for too long. *chuckles*
Can you imagine running this town on your own?!//Oh, Mayor <NpcName>Connor</> is good at it. We love him.
Frankly, I don’t know who would do it, if Mayor <NpcName>Connor</> didn’t.//<portrait=normal>I certainly couldn’t! Too much responsibility for me.

<NpcName>Ling</> is your girl if you wanna know more about kelp, coral reef, and that stuff.//<portrait=happy><NpcName>Sunny</> and <NpcName>Jim</> can help with your fishing problem.//<portrait=normal>Hmm… What else… What else?
And the blacksmiths make weapons. You know that, right?
I wouldn’t consider this a small town. There are so many people living here!
My goodness. The islanders are hard to keep up with!
Don’t you just love <NpcName>Karen</>’s haircut? The lady working at Pufferfish...//<portrait=happy>That was me. I did that!
Can you believe it’s the weekend already?
Well, not quite the weekend yet, but almost. It’s Thursday, which means tomorrow is Friday.
What do I do on the weekends? Hmm… That’s a great question.
I help clean up the community center.//The place is often empty. Who knows how much dust it accumulates.
Sometimes I work on Sundays. If there’s nothing better to do, that is.
That’s right, I’m a busy girl, <PlayerName>$player</>!
I wouldn’t consider this a small town. There are so many people living here!
My goodness. The islanders are hard to keep up with!//<portrait=surprised>They always have things going on in their lives.
Sometimes I work on Sundays. If there’s nothing better to do, that is.
It’s always close to midnight when <NpcName>Frank</> gets home, but I still lock the door around eightish.
Oh, no, I’m not worried about break-ins. I just don’t want any visitors.//<portrait=normal>Besides, <NpcName>Frank</> has his own key, so he can let himself into the house whenever.
Oh, no no... I don’t gossip. I extract and share information...//<portrait=happy>YES! Sort of like the morning news.
I’m doing a public service to make sure we all know who our neighbors are. It’s not an easy job, you know. Never once have I been thanked.
Having a job, and all, leaves me little time to keep up with the neighbors.

One time, while I was sick, everyone started going through these massive life changes. By the time I was back on my feet, there was a new scientist in town, a huge corporation was trying to drill up the island, and <NpcName>Valentina</>’s dad had missed a visit!
Having a job, and all, leaves me little time to keep up with the neighbors.

Saw you at the beach last week, in and out of the inn? What were you doing, visiting the inn so often?
*chuckles* Excuse me for prying.
People should always tell the truth, because, gosh! Lies are hard to remember.//Also, I don’t wanna be caught spreading false information, here. My good name is on the line.
You can count on me for a good haircut.//So, if you ever want to change…umm…that, just drop by the salon.
<NpcName>Frank</> has been the grill master for the past decade, so I think he would do that again this year…//Oh, you know, for the Cherry Blossom Festival.
The man loves the job. It would probably break his heart, seeing other people doing it.
<NpcName>Charles</> does have red hair, but he also colors it red to keep it bright.
If you ask me, I say it’s because the poor thing wants to keep a bit of brightness in his life.
I don’t gossip. I obtain and share information… So, sort of like the morning news.
I’m doing a public service to make sure we all know who our neighbors are.//<portrait=annoyed>It’s not an easy job, you know. Never once have I been thanked.
Here comes summer!
With all this humidity, it’s going to be one sweaty summer for us.
Well, of course, I still volunteer at the school. Why wouldn’t I?
Has summer been kind to you, <PlayerName>$player</>? We left some food on the counter last night, and one of the cats ate it.
So now I’m just keeping an eye on <NpcName>Peanut</> and <NpcName>Butter</>. Hopefully nobody gets a tummy ache.
I’m going right back home as soon as I’m done with work. I have to keep an eye on the cats tonight.
I caught them trying to open the fridge door this morning. I’m not about to let that go.
I’m going right back home as soon as I’m done with work. I have to keep an eye on the cats tonight.
I caught them trying to open the fridge door this morning. I’m not about to let that go.
I’m going right back home as soon as I’m done with work. I’m feeling a bit ill today.
I think I should eat some soup and lie down.
Have you got one of those calendars in your house, <PlayerName>$player</>? You can keep track of people’s birthdays at your own convenience.
My good friend <NpcName>Bree</>’s birthday is coming up. I’m gonna see if I have some jackfruit lying around. She loves that stuff.
If not, I guess a jar of jam will do.
I have <NpcName>Ben</> looking out for some orchids this fall. I hope he comes through.
The thing about winter, though, is that not many people are out and about. It’s hard to socialize when we’re all cooped up inside our houses.
You know, <NpcName>Bree</> came from a big city, just like you… She had a fancy modeling job right before she married <NpcName>Walter</>.
She said it was love at first sight. I don’t remember exactly how they met, but she told me it was some sort of work event.
I don’t know what work event, <PlayerName>$player</>! I’m not a nosy person. *winks*
You know, <NpcName>Bree</> came from a big city, just like you… She had a fancy modeling job right before she married <NpcName>Walter</>.
She said it was love at first sight. I don’t remember exactly how they met, but she told me it was some sort of work event.
I don’t know what work event, <PlayerName>$player</>! I’m not a nosy person.
Here comes winter!
I’m going right back home as soon as I’m done with work. I have to keep an eye on the cats tonight.
I caught them trying to open the fridge door this morning. I’m not about to let that go.
I’m going to the Winter Fair on Sunday.
I have some business to take care of on Saturday, so I can’t go. But I heard <NpcName>Sam</> and <NpcName>Emily</> are going then.
<NpcName>Frank</> said I would make a great detective.
I know he was teasing me, but I have to agree with him. *chuckles* I was flattered.
<NpcName>Frank</> said I would make a great detective.
I know he was teasing me, but I don’t object. I think I would make a good detective.
Rainy days make me so hungry for some reason. You too, yeah?
So annoying. I have things to do, you see. I can’t sit and eat all day.
Perfect weather for some spicy red curry!
The cats hate the rain. Now that I think about it, they don’t really like sunshine either. Hmm…
Watch your step! It’s super slippery.
Ugh… I need to wash my shoes tomorrow.//<portrait=annoyed>They get super muddy! I hope it won’t be raining, though.
Rainy days make me so hungry for some reason. You too, yeah?
Perfect weather for some spicy red curry!
Ooh… What are you doing here so late in the evening, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Did I ever tell you about my first date with <NpcName>Frank</>?
Oh, good fairies! Here comes a story.//<portrait=normal>He took me on a picnic. When the big day came, it was storming really hard.

Storming just like this. But we didn’t wanna cancel because it was our first date.//<portrait=normal>I was curious about him. You know…when we got to the picnic spot, we stayed underneath a tree…to stay dry.//And he went on and on telling stories, trying to keep me interested.

I was so busy listening to his story, trying to make out what <NpcName>Frank</> was saying – mind you, it was storming! – that we both forgot to keep an eye on the picnic basket.//<portrait=surprised>It blew away! We had NO food.
Oh, you silly goose! Of course, you wanna hear a story.//<portrait=surprised>Oh! Here comes a story. He took me for a picnic.//<portrait=normal>When the big day came, it was storming really hard.

Storming just like this. But we didn’t wanna cancel because it was our first date.//<portrait=normal>I was curious about him. You know…when we got to the picnic spot, we stayed underneath a tree…to stay dry.//And he went on and on telling stories, trying to keep me interested.

I was so busy listening to his story, trying to make out what <NpcName>Frank</> was saying – mind you, it was storming! – that we both forgot to keep an eye on the picnic basket.//<portrait=surprised>It blew away! We had NO food.
The cats hate the rain.//Now that I think about it, they don’t really like sunshine either. Hmm…
It is one windy day! Protect your head, <PlayerName>$player</>.
I should’ve worn my hat.
It’s so windy outside.
The snow is kinda pretty, isn’t it?
My favorite winter spot is next to a fireplace.//Bet it’s yours too!
Ahh! It’s so cold! I’m ready for summer.
You can still grow things like snowdrops and tea leaves, right?
Ahh! It’s so cold! I’m ready for summer.
<NpcName>Kenny</> mentioned that more animals get sick when it snows. Are your animals doing okay?
Hopefully the cats won’t go out today. It’s way too cold for them.
The snow makes everything look so clean.
Ahh! It’s so cold! I’m ready for summer.
*shivers*
I volunteer my time here once a week. Usually on Mondays.//I get fewer clients at the salon at the beginning of the week, so Mondays are perfect for me.
I think I’ve gotten some wood chips inside my shoes.
It’s inevitable.//<portrait=concerned>Every time I walk here, wood chips… Wood chips! Wood chips!
You know <NpcName>Dippa</>? The painter? They used to perform in some sort of acrobatic group.
I don’t think they do anymore. They threw their back out or something.
I’m just enjoying the weather. What are you doing, <PlayerName>$player</>? You seem to be in a rush.

I always wonder why <NpcName>Bree</> didn’t purchase your grandparents' plot of land.//<portrait=surprised>She seems to be at the lookout area all the time. So she <Italic>clearly</> enjoys the view from up there.
It’s a mystery to me, because the lady has money.//<portrait=happy>But hey, at least now we have you.
Don’t be silly. I’m not snooping around.
I’m merely enjoying the town. If there happens to be information I can pick up, that’s just a happy coincidence.
You can get really good at cooking just by watching the cooking channel. So many super easy recipes.
I don’t cook very well. Anything beyond a simple salad is out of my league.
I’m not looking forward to going home. Nobody did the dishes before we left this morning.//<portrait=normal>So the house is a huge mess right now.
I can’t make everyone look good, <PlayerName>$player</>! I’m not a magician.
But I can work on your hair. That’s a great canvas you’ve got.
<NpcName>Peanut</> and <NpcName>Butter</> need to go outside more. They love their couches too much.
This one time, I gave <NpcName>Dippa</> hot cocoa for their birthday because I didn’t have anything else ready.
And frankly, if I’m being honest, I forgot.//<portrait=happy>But it turned out to be one of <NpcName>Dippa</>’s favorite things!//<portrait=normal>I got lucky, I guess.
Who would’ve thought I would see you here! Of all places.
You can count on me for a good haircut.//So, if you ever want to change…umm…that, just drop by the salon.
This building is old. As old as this town, I believe.//<portrait=happy>It does't show though, huh?
I think the tavern is the only other building as old as this one.
I’m here to promote my salon. Haircut, hair color. You know the drill.
Oh, imagine if people start coming to this island just to go to my salon!/<portrait=normal>Thinking about that makes me so excited!
<NpcName>Emily</> should really come here with me. We could have a chat over cheese.
Make sure to check on <NpcName>Stephen</>! He is a delight…with his little claws.//So cute.
What a smart idea to put a sewing machine out here, huh?//So kind.
Don’t be silly, <PlayerName>$player</>! I'm not snooping around.
I’m here to check on my friends and see what they’ve been up to.//<portrait=surprised>And, you know, to see what’s going on with <NpcName>Anthony</> lately.
<NpcName>Anthony</> is <NpcName>Valentina</>’s dad. <NpcName>Rafael</>’s cousin.//<portrait=annoyed>Keep up, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Ooh… What are you doing here so often?
Don’t worry! My lips are sealed.
My aunt told me that a long time ago, when she was a little girl, she and her friends used to watch the area near the villa at midnight to see if there actually was a ghost living there.
Yeah, this was before the villa was even built. My nana would get upset because Aunt <NpcName>Abel</> would stay up too late. Do you believe in that sort of stuff, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Today is <NpcName>Frank</>’s birthday. *whispers* I got him a gift.//I’m gonna give the present to him later, when we get home.
Drinks on me, <PlayerName>$player</>.
To <NpcName>Frank</>!
All right… Keep being you, <PlayerName>$player</>!

Special.SourceString: Nah Thanks though. I still have work.

Text.SourceString: It smells a bit musky here, doesn’t it? Like sandalwood.
<NpcName>Betty</> said that’s the smell of good times and old friends.//I think she’s right.
Being an adult is mostly just washing dishes nonstop.
I’m not looking forward to going home. Nobody did the dishes this morning before we left.//<portrait=normal>So the house is a huge mess right now.
Being an adult is mostly just washing dishes nonstop.
Once you sit down on one of these sofas, it’s hard to get up//<portrait=concerned>I get why these cats don’t like going outside.
<NpcName>Frank</> works late often, so I usually get to hog the TV all night.
I think I’ll go to bed soon…//It’s been a long day for me, I could use some extra sleep.
My request?! You follow through.
Thank you, <PlayerName>$player</>. I know I can count on you. Dinner tonight is going to be special.
